@zilveer @kyuupichan for blackcoin we use `LegacyRPCDaemon` that takes the decomposed block and creates a fake/simulated raw block so it can be processed by the rest of the code.

The problem you are facing is due to the blackcoin daemon not returning the coinbase transaction from an orphaned block (because it is not correctly indexed due to a bug). In issue #315 I wrote about a potential solution.

If you want to make blackcoin work right now you have to rebuild it with the following patch. Keep in mind that it doesn't have great performance.

```
diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index dbb54d5e..f02382ba 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -860,6 +860,24 @@ bool GetTransaction(const uint256 &hash, CTransaction &tx, uint256 &hashBlock)
                 hashBlock = block.GetHash();
             return true;
         }
+        // look for transaction in disconnected blocks to find orphaned CoinBase and CoinStake transactions
+        BOOST_FOREACH(PAIRTYPE(const uint256, CBlockIndex*)& item, mapBlockIndex)
+        {
+            CBlockIndex* pindex = item.second;
+            if (pindex == pindexBest || pindex->pnext != 0)
+                continue;
+            CBlock block;
+            if (!block.ReadFromDisk(pindex))
+                continue;
+            BOOST_FOREACH(const CTransaction& txOrphan, block.vtx)
+            {
+                if (txOrphan.GetHash() == hash)
+                {
+                    tx = txOrphan;
+                    return true;
+                }
+            }
+        }
     }
     return false;
 }
```

