As-is, there is no way in the presentation to associate an error with the appropriate field. Maybe the idea I have in mind is too simplistic with potential problems that I have not thought of yet, but I would think you would just follow the schema. Thus:
```
{
    "_missing_required": ["name"],
    "id": <Err(must be number)>,
    "price": <Err(must not be less than 0)>,
    "tags": [None,<Err(must be string)>,None,<Err(must be string)>],
    "stock": {
        "retail": <Err(must be number)>,
    }
}
```

In practice, I really don't know how well this would work for forms. I suppose one would have to walk the schema to generate the form, and along the way pull out instance data and errors based on the current key.

@plypaul arbitrary means a SIGKILL in this case which leaves any process in an undetermined state. So the chances of it to occur are small (it also needs to coincide with the time between the change to scheduled and the executor receiving it at a kill of the scheduler). There is also a small chance the executor gets killed which would leave the task in limbo too. 

To remove no 1. The with_for_update needs to wrap the "send" to the executor. The transaction to the db will then fail in case of a kill and the state will not be changed. To remove number 2 probably a kind of garbage collection needs to be added (at the time of checking for zombie tasks?). 

Changes are slim and in general one should not go around kill -9 processes.

这是源代码
class WeChatSigner(object):
    """WeChat data signer"""

    def __init__(self, delimiter=b''):
        self._data = []
        self._delimiter = to_binary(delimiter)

    def add_data(self, *args):
        """Add data to signer"""
        for data in args:
            self._data.append(to_binary(data))

    @property
    def signature(self):
        """Get data signature"""
        self._data.sort()
        str_to_sign = self._delimiter.join(self._data)
        return hashlib.sha1(str_to_sign).hexdigest()

 这是我写的
def generate_sign(params):
    # 生成待签名的字符串
    signed_array = []
    for k, v in params.items():
        # 参数值为空，不参与签名
        if v != "":
            signed_array.append("%s=%s" % (k, v))
    to_be_signed_str = "&".join(sorted(signed_array))
    signed_str = hashlib.sha1(to_be_signed_str).hexdigest()
    return signed_str

