You can customize the parser and register it over the sqlite adapter:

```python
from pydal.parsers import parsers, for_type
from pydal.parsers.sqlite import SQLiteParser
from pydal.adapters.sqlite import SQLite
@parsers.register_for(SQLite)
class CustomTimeParser(SQLiteParser):
    @for_type('time')
    def _time(self, value):
        return value
```

I think the reason we are running into this problem is because `PytorchSeq2SeqWrapper` and `PytorchSeq2VecWrapper` implement a lot of the same stuff in forward surrounding reordering the batch, which should maybe be separate. What about something like this:

```
def sorted_forwards(rnn_function, sequence, lengths, state):
