@jorenham, `post_migrate` should also work (it was actually one of the avenues I explored) but it has the disadvantage of not being optional, as in you wouldn't be able to run `migrate` without running `sync_page_translation_fields`, which is less than ideal. `sync_page_translation_fields` only needs to be ran when a new language is added which is less frequent than schema changes.

Having a nested app with a `migrate` command make things more versatile, keeping all options available to the developer.

Having said that, if you prefer to use the  `post_migrate` signal in your test setup, instead of adding `'wagtail_modeltranslation.migrate',` to your `INSTALLED_APPS`, that's certainly a valid scenario.

